  "decision_conditions": [
    "The cumulative width of the existing single storey side/rear extension and proposed single storey rear extension would have a width greater than half the width of the original dwelling house and therefore would not comply with permitted development as outlined under Schedule 2, Part 1, Class A of The Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 and the MHCLG Permitted development rights for householders Technical Guidance (September 2019).",
    "The applicant should note drawing number 24:041 A seems to indicate that there is marginal infringement over the boundary line. As with all permitted development, all of the development needs to be within the curtilage of the application site, in this instance 2 Little Gaynes Gardens, Upminster.",
    "Should a planning application be submitted, it is suggested that this anomaly should be corrected on any revised drawings or that the relevant notice is served on the adjoining neighbour."
